{
  "stem": "27390.8",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When we stopped outside Theresienstadt-- so, the German guards were also very exhausted.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They had been with us for four weeks without any change of clothes or any rest.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So the Czech partisans came along-- we didn't know they were partisans-- but they came along, and they took this picture.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They took-- I got hold of this picture afterwards, not at the time when they took it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they took this picture of us, and they asked the guards if they would like a bath and some food, some hot food.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So naturally they jumped to it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they took them off from the train, and they went away with them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we never saw these guards again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They never came back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were taken in-- but this was still- the Germans were still in control of this area.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we didn't know what's happening.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were taken into the ghetto, the Theresienstadt ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we were taken into a bath, and as we came into the bath, we undressed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in the middle of-- I keep saying bath.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was showers.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In the middle of having this shower, there was a direct hit, and the lights went out, a hit from a- not from a bomb, from a heavy artillery shell.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we all fell to the floor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we lay on the floor like this.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there was a lot of shelling going on from both sides.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "On one side the Russians were shelling, and the other side the Germans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we were in a sort of a valley.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it carried on for a few hours.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then in the morning, it was still night one of the boys got up, looked out of the window, and he heard a noise.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
